    <title>Combined summary - Bitcoin address TTL &amp; key expiration?</title>
    <updated>2023-06-09T00:54:18.674134+00:00</updated>
    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/bitcoin-dev/2014-July/006232.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>The context discusses the limitations of Payment Protocol and Bitcoin addresses in various scenarios. One suggestion is to limit the lifetime of a Bitcoin address to prevent accidental sending of bitcoins to expired pubkey/pkh. Address reuse is also an issue that concerns Bitcoin developers. Although wallets and services can already ignore transactions using an address more than once, there may be issues with race attacks if this is implemented immediately.Furthermore, BIP70 has been found to be insufficient for longer-term payment relationships such as subscriptions. Negotiating HD wallet details enables users to use a new address every time, which is necessary for recurring payments. While BIP70 satisfies some use cases, designing extensions to address situations where BIP70 is not feasible or suboptimal is necessary.Despite these challenges, several companies and organizations, such as the Bitcoin Improvement Proposal program and BitPay, are working towards implementing Payment Protocol on the blockchain. If successful, it could revolutionize the way we use blockchain technology and lead to increased adoption rates. The context emphasizes the need for smarter contract language and addressing the limitations of Bitcoin addresses to achieve this goal.Payment Protocol aims to provide a more efficient and cost-effective way to communicate data on the blockchain. However, its adoption rate has been somewhat slow due to various reasons such as regulatory challenges, technical challenges, and lack of awareness about blockchain technology among the general public.The use of Payment Protocol could potentially revolutionize the way we use blockchain technology and increase adoption rates. However, several challenges need to be addressed before it becomes a reality. The Bitcoin Improvement Proposal (BIP) program and BitPay are already working towards implementing Payment Protocol on the blockchain. Discussions about extending BIP 70 to allow for negotiating HD wallet details and proposing an expiry time for addresses have been ongoing.</summary>
